node.text:
Since 1969, Democratic presidents have appointed 4 Supreme Court justices, while Republicans have appointed 16 (5 of them by presidents who lost the popular vote). McConnell refused to even hold a hearing on Obama's nominee.

Expanding the Supreme Court is not radical. It's essential. Thank you to @MondaireJones for setting the record straight and co-sponsoring legislation to make it happen.

May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich I fear we're about to discover what happens when a horrendous hurricane rams into an area with low vaccination rates, high COVID, and already-full hospitals. Sadly, these are not unrelated.'.

node.text: Hopes and prayers for the people of New Orleans now suffering the triple-whammy of COVID, Hurricane Ida, and shortages of hospital beds. But isn’t it about time America stopped relying on hopes and prayers to prevent the foreseeable and preventable?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Robert Reich on August 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich So let me get this straight: Republican legislators want to arm teachers to protect students from school shooters, but don't want teachers to wear masks to protect students from a deadly virus?'.

node.text: Does this make sense to anyone?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Robert Reich on August 28, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich Freedom doesn't mean you have the right to jeopardize the heath of others, incubate worse strains of a deadly virus, and shut down the economy.'.

node.text: Freedom isn’t recklessness.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Robert Reich on August 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich During the war in Afghanistan, Congress gave 5 companies $2 trillion: Boeing Raytheon General Dynamics Northrop Grumman Lockheed Martin War and oligarchy are a dangerous combination.'.

node.text: War is a racket.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Robert Reich on August 26, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich Never forget that the senators who claim we can't afford a bold budget reconciliation package had no problem wasting $2 trillion on a failed, unwinnable war in Afghanistan.'.

Photo by Robert Reich on August 25, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich "How 'How can we afford paid leave?" "How can we afford child care?" "How can we afford free community college?" "How can we afford bold climate action?" U.S. billionaires added $1.8 trilion to their wealth during the pandemic alone. We tax them. That's how we can afford it.'.

node.text: We have the money to pass a budget bill that tackles the climate crisis and massively invests in building a fairer America. The richest 1% of Americans control $41 trillion in wealth. Just tax them.
